P/HARCOURT – Culture has been identified as an avenue to unite people irrespective of religious beliefs. It was on this note that the people of Andoni Local Government Area of Rivers State gathered in their numbers to celebrate their cultural heritage after a long period of layoff because of insecurity in the area. The indigenes of the Council also used the event to call on investors to harness the natural resources in the area. This was backed up by the boat regatta organized by the council authority at Asarama and attended by people from all walks of life. Speaking at the occasion, Member Federal House of Representatives, Hon Awaji-inombek Abiante, who lauded efforts of the council boss for the initiative stated that over the years the people could not gather to celebrate cultural heritage as a result of the insecurity that plagued the area for years. PHACCIMA President Marks Annual Fishing Festival, Speaks On Need… Rivers Govt Bans Cart Pushing, Indiscriminate Posting Of Advert Abiante reassured the chairman of his unflinching support for the development of the area which will become the envy of other local government areas of the state. On his part, chairman of the council Barr Erastus Awortu said the event revealed the passion of the people, their willingness for peace and the crave for development of the area. The Chairman explained that the environment is endowed with natural resources surrounded by aquatic lives, hence the need for investors to look the way of the local government. Barr Awortu added that memo had been written to the state, National and foreign bodies to attract their attention to the tourism potentials of the area. “We are blessed with natural resources. That is why we are calling on investors and tourists to take advantage of our wildlife and the vast body of water surrounding us”.